Quicker, fuller, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Tosses it up, full again, around middle and off. Ben Stokes steps down the wicket and pushes it back to the bowler.

Cut him in half! A length ball, jagging back in, around the fourth stump line. Ben Foakes looks to block this but he gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball sneaks past through the off pole. A close one!
Fuller length, on the off stump. Ben Foakes plays it towards the point straight to the fielder.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ben Foakes strides forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Good length, outside off. Ben Foakes let's that ball go to the keeper.
Lungi Ngidi goes a bit shorter now, maintains the same line outside off. Ben Foakes gets on his toes and blocks it out.
Fuller length, down the leg. Ben Foakes tries to flick it towards fine leg but misses it and it goes straight to the keeper.

Beautifully bowled! A huge appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! Tosses this one up, it pitches around leg and straightens. Ben Stokes presses forward and looks to block this but he misses and gets hit on his pads. Dean Elgar decides to go up for the review! Nothing on UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking indicates it was missing the wickets and it was the umpire's call on the impact as well. The on-field decision stands.
Good length, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes blocks it on the front foot towards the bowler.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Ben Stokes prods forward and nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller length, onto the off stump channel. Ben Stokes defends it on the front foot back down the pitch.

Top edge but lands safely! A fuller ball, slower through the air, around middle. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps this one. The ball though goes off the top edge over the backward point fielder for a brace.
Fuller length, onto the stump. Ben Stokes tries to block this one on the front foot but gets an inside edge and the ball goes towards the square leg region for a single.
Lungi Ngidi sprits in from 'round the wicket. and serves a length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes the ball down the wicket straight to the bowler.
Lungi Ngidi bowls another length ball, outside off, at 135 clicks. Ben Stokes shoulders his arms at it.
Fuller length, angling in. Ben Stokes gets his bat down in time and hits it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
This one swings away from the left-hander, outside off, a length ball, at 136 kph. Ben Stokes does not fiddle with that one.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes lets that one go through to the keeper.
Simon Harmer comes in from over the wicket and delivers a fuller ball, around middle and off. Ben Foakes prods forward and blocks it out.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the long on fielder for a single.
Tosses it up, full and around middle. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch and blocks it out towards cover.
Quicker delivery, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the mid on region for a single.
Spinning into the right-hander, shorter in length, around off. Ben Foakes stays in his crease and tucks it towards square leg.
On a good length, onto the stump. Ben Foakes blocks on the front foot.
A good-length delivery, this one lands outside off and shapes away. Ben Stokes offers no shot to that.
FOUR! Fuller ball, onto the stump. Ben Stokes dances down the ground and punches it straight down the ground for a boundary.
Pulls his length back now, around middle, at 139 clicks. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Fuller length, down the leg side. Ben Stokes lets that one go through to the keeper.
Angling in, around middle and leg, a length ball. Ben Stokes looks to block this but the ball goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket for a single.
EDGE! on a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes tries to defend it but gets an outside edge and it went towards the third man region for a couple.
Loopy ball, full, around middle. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and sweeps it along the ground towards square leg for a single.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Tosses it up, full, around off. Ben Foakes defends it out solidly off the front foot.
Tad fuller, onto the stumps, quicker through the air. Ben Foakes defends it on the front foot.
Quicker, fuller as well, around middle and off. Ben Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid on fielder for a single.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes knocks this towards cover-point and takes a run.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes drives it straight to the fielder at mid off.
Lungi Ngidi continues bowling full and slightly outside off, Ben Stokes blocks this towards point.
On a good length, angling in. Ben Stokes pushes it straight to the fielder at silly mid on.

FOUR! High-quality shot from Ben Stokes! Lungi Ngidi goes full and angles this into the off pole. Ben Stokes punches this down the ground to the left of the bowler and the ball raises to the straight long on fence for a beautiful boundary. Great timing on this shot and Ben Stokes is looking dangerous here.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the mid on fielder.
Simon Harmer flights this one full and outside off, Ben Stokes shuffles down the wicket and clips the ball to short mid on.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes dances down the pitch and plays it towards the mid-wicket region for a double.
Simon Harmer bowls this a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes gets across to the off side and tucks the ball towards backward square leg.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it off the front foot.

FOUR! Ben Foakes gets this one away! Simon Harmer flights this one full and angling into the off pole, Ben Foakes comes down the wicket and clips the ball towards deep mid-wicket for four runs. Both batters have been aggressive towards spin and are getting some quick runs here.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it off the front foot.
Kagiso Rabada begins a new spell with a good-length delivery angling into middle from 'round the wicket. Ben Stokes clips this towards deep backward square leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes lets that one go through to the keeper.
Bowls this on a good length and wide outside the off stump. Ben Foakes leaves this one alone.
On a good length, onto the middle stump line. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the silly mid off fielder.

Kagiso Rabada goes full and angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes tucks this with soft hands towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single. That brings up the fifty partnership between these two and South Africa will be really worried as it has come in quick time.
Slower delivery, fuller length, onto the stump. Kagiso Rabada tries to bowl something different but Ben Stokes reads that one and blocks it very comfortably.
Simon Harmer loops this full and just outside off, Ben Foakes clips this to the right of mid-wicket.
On a good length, outside off stump. Simon Harmer bowls this one slower through the air and beats Ben Foakes due to lack of pace and the ball hits his front pad.
Continues to flight this full and outside off, Ben Foakes shimmies down the wicket and works this ball to short mid on.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it off the front foot down to the fielder at mid-off.
Bowls this one a touch quicker, full and turning into the batter from outside off. Ben Foakes gets beaten by the spin as the ball hits his body and falls down into the pitch.
Fuller length, on the off stump line. Ben Foakes walks down the pitch and flicks it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Kagiso Rabada continues bowling 'round the wicket to the southpaw. This is on a good length and outside off. Ben Stokes continues to be disciplined as he leaves this one alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and punches it towards the fielder at deep point for a single.
Kagiso Rabada serves this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes strokes this to the left of mid off and takes a single.
Bowls this on a good length and in line with the off stump, Ben Foakes stands tall and blocks the ball back down the pitch.
Goes short this time and angles this one down leg. Ben Stokes ducks comfortably under this one.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves that one away through to the keeper.
Simon Harmer fires this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes uses his wrists and clips the ball towards short mid on.
Tad shorter, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes dabs it down to square leg.
Floats this one full and wider outside off, Ben Foakes taps this towards point.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes shuffles across and defends it to silly point region.
Simon Harmer bowls a quicker delivery full and fired into the pads. Ben Foakes clips this towards short fine leg.
Short of length, outside off. Ben Foakes chops it off the back foot towards deep backward point for a single.
Kagiso Rabada pitches this one up, around off. Ben Foakes clips it down the ground towards mid on. A single taken.
'Round the wicket, back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes punches it off the back foot towards the deep cover region for a couple.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Fuler length, outside off. Ben Stokes drives off the front foot straight to the fielder at short extra cover.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Ben Stokes is happy to let that go through to the keeper.
Fuller length, angling in. Ben Stokes punches it down to mid on fielder for a quick single.
Lovely ball! Turn and bounce on that occasion! He pitches it around off, it spins away outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes sit down on one knee and misses the reverse sweep.
Tosses it up, full and around middle and off. Ben Stokes presses forward and blocks it out.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards short extra cover.
Outside off, fuller one. Ben Stokes pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes blocks it off the front foot straight to the bowler.

Keshav Maharaj serves this full and around leg, gets the ball to turn sharply and beats the outside edge of the bat. Goes on to hit the back leg and there is a huge appeal from the players around the bat. The umpire raises his finger and after some contemplation, Ben Foakes decides to review this. UltraEdge shows no bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates that it has pitched outside leg. The on-field decision has been reversed and Ben Foakes survives.
On a good length, onto the stump. Ben Foakes defends it of the front foot.

Another huge appeal! Keshav Maharaj bowls this full and pitching on leg, Ben Foakes looks to work the leg side but misses and hits his pads. This one was much closer but they do not review. Replays show that this would have been umpire's call as it was clipping to top of leg stump.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Foakes flicks it towards the deep square leg for a single.
Keshav Maharaj flights this one full and outside off, Ben Stokes strokes this through covers and gets a couple of runs.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes defends solidly off the front foot.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes gets down the wicket and hits the ball back to the bowler.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes drives it straight to the bowler.
Simon Harmer serves this one a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes goes back in the crease to negotiate the extra bounce and defends this solidly
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid-off fielder.
Simon Harmer flights this one full and outside off, getting the ball to turn back in. Ben Foakes blocks this down towards short leg.

NO BALL AND FOUR! This has been slapped away! Simon Harmer bowls a really high full toss in line with the stumps. That's a gift by Simon Harmer. Ben Foakes smashes it towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. The umpire indicates that this will be a no ball for height.
Shorter one, outside off. Ben Foakes hangs back and blocks it out solidly. That will be Lunch on Day 2!
Keshav Maharaj comes over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, spinning in, around middle. Ben Stokes leans forward and blocks it out.
Swing and a miss! A fuller one, spinning down leg. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee to reverse-sweep this one but he misses.
Quicker, shorter, outside off. Ben Stokes hangs back and blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out off the back foot.
Quicker, flatter and fuller in length. Ben Stokes misses his reverse-sweep once again and fails to get any connection on it.
Tosses this one up, full, around off. Ben Stokes prods forward and blocks it out.
Simon Harmer starts off with a shorter ball, spinning in, around off. Ben Foakes rocks back and defends it out.
Quick again, short and outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it through point off the back foot for a single.
Come 'round the wicket, and serves a fuller one, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it watchfully.
Shorter ball, around middle, spinning away. Ben Stokes uses the depth of his crease and defends it out.
Fuller one, around middle. Ben Stokes pushes it back to the bowler.
Pitches it up again, around middle and off. Ben Stokes prods forward and defends it out.
This one comes in with the arm, full, around the pads. Ben Foakes leans forward and defends it out.
Slower through the air, full again, around off. Ben Foakes strides forward and defends it out.
Drifting in, around middle and leg, full again. Ben Foakes shows the full face of the bat and blocks it out.
Tosses this one up, around middle and leg, full in length. Ben Foakes flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Outside off, loopy ball, pitched up as well. Ben Foakes is solid in his defense.
Spinning away, full, around off. Ben Foakes blocks it out.
Shorter one, this one lands around middle and spins away. Ben Stokes rocks back and defends it out.
Quick and full, around middle and off. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch and pushes it past mid on. Only a single.
Spinning in, shorter one, around middle. Ben Foakes uses the depth of the crease and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.

Beaten! Well bowled! Tosses it up, this one pitches around off and spins away sharply. Ben Stokes gets down on his knee and misses his sweeps shot. Kyle Verreynne gathers the ball and whips the bails off. The replay shows that Ben Stokes is foot was well grounded.
This one comes in with the angle, around middle and off, fuller one. Ben Stokes leans forward and defends it out.
Drifting it in on the pads, on the pads, shorter one. Ben Stokes nudges it towards mid-wicket. A good over from Simon Harmer comes to an end.
Keshav Maharaj flights this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back to the bowler.
Keshav Maharaj fires on full that straightens after pitching. Ben Foakes misses his block and gets hit on the pads.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this short and outside off, Ben Stokes guides this to backward point and takes a run.
A fraction short and outside off, Ben Stokes rocks back in the crease and punches it through covers for a single.
Flights this one full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this to the leg side.
Fires this one slightly short and into the pads, Ben Foakes tucks this to short fine leg.
Simon Harmer flights this one full and in line with the stumps, Ben Stokes fends this solidly down the pitch.
Slower through the air, fuller in length, in the channel outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it back to Simon Harmer.
Tosses it up, serves it full, around middle and off. Ben Stokes takes a stride forward and defends it out.
Bowls this full and just outside off, Ben Stokes pushes at this and gets and inside edge onto pads.
This is full as well and straighter, Ben Stokes blocks this back to the bowler.
Slower in the air and outside off, Ben Stokes gets a stride forward and taps the ball to short cover.
Keshav Maharaj begins with a shorter delivery outside off, Ben Foakes uses his wrists and clips the ball towards short leg.
Fires one full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes clips this through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
This is full and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this to the leg side.
Continues bowling full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes defends the straight into the pitch.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes clips this towards backward square leg.
Keshav Maharaj flights this full outside off, Ben Foakes strokes this straight to cover.
Simon Harmer tosses this one full and outside the off stump, Ben Stokes drives the ball past cover for a run.
Bowls this one quicker in the air and full outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
Floats this one full and into the stumps, Ben Foakes clips this through mid-wicket for a single
Simon Harmer flights this one full as well and outside off, Ben Stokes knocks this towards long off and takes one.
Back of a length, turning in, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes flicks it to the fielder at square leg.
Another one turning in, short ball, around middle. Ben Foakes defends it towards short leg.
Keshav Maharaj loops this one full and outside the off pole, Ben Stokes defends this towards mid off.
This on a short and outside off, gives Ben Stokes room to go back in his crease and slash this towards deep cover for two runs.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this a touch short and outside off, Ben Stokes gets back and pulls this towards mid-wicket for a run.
Flights this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
This is full and well and angles into the pads, Ben Foakes clips the ball down towards short leg.
This one is fired into the leg stump on a fuller length, Ben Foakes nudges this down towards the short leg fielder.
Fuller one, tad quicker at 85 clicks, around middle. Ben Stokes presents the full face of the bat and defends it out.
Bowls this fuller, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes defends it on the front foot.
Tosses it up, serves it full, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it out solidly.
Tad shorter, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and defends it.
Loopy ball, quicker again, around off. Ben Stokes prods forward and defends it out watchfully.
Quicker one, fuller length, onto the stump. Ben Stokes moves to back foot and defends it late.
Drifting it on the pads, fuller in length. Ben Foakes leans forward and flicks it just away from the fielder at short leg.
Fuller delivery, onto the leg stump. Ben Foakes pushes it towards short leg fielder.
Tosses it up, a touch quicker at 86 clicks, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes works it away towards the fielder at mid on.
Shorter ball, onto the off stump. Ben Foakes defends it solidly on the front foot.
Back of a length, spinning away, at 82 kph. Ben Foakes uses the depth of his crease and knocks it towards mid-wicket. No run there!
Flights this one full, outside off. Ben Foakes defends it very comfortably.
Simon Harmer comes in from 'round the wicket and serves a shorter ball, spinning away, around off. Ben Foakes hangs back and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes pushes it towards long on for a single.

Tosses this one up, very full on this occasion, around off. Ben Stokes presses forward and drives it gently through cover. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
Bowls this full, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes gets an leading edge towards the cover region.

SIX! Ben Stokes brings up his fifty in style! A crucial knock from the skipper! A fuller one ball, tosses it up, around middle. Ben Stokes shimmies down the pitch and dispatches this one over long on for a biggie!
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes comes forward and blocks it back to bowler.
Anrich Nortje begins with a fuller ball, angling in, around middle and leg, at 138 clicks. Ben Foakes flicks it through square leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Ben Stokes was in two minds about whether to go for a shot or leave. In the end, he lets that one go to the keeper.
A good-length delivery, outside off, at 140 kph. Ben Stokes cover the line of the ball and blocks it out towards cover.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Stokes defends it straight to the bowler.
Anrich Nortje speeds in from 'round the wicket, outside off, a length ball. Ben Stokes manages to get an outside edge towards gully. A single taken.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Foakes looks to clip this one but misses and goes off the pads straight down to fine leg for a leg bye.
Loopy ball, very full, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes dances down the pitch and flicks it through mid-wicket. Two taken!
Fuller length, onto off stump. Ben Foakes guides it towards the point region.
Shortish ball, spinning away, around middle, at 80 kph. Ben Foakes rocks back and blocks it out onto the deck.
Fuller one, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes flicks it towards the mid wicket region.
Fuller one this time, around off, tosses it up, Ben Foakes drives it to the fielder at mid off.
Quicker delivery, down leg. Ben Foakes tries to work it towards the fine leg region but finds a fielder at backward square leg.
An overpitched delivery, outside off. Ben Stokes drives this one away from his body through cover for a brace.
Fuller length, around off. Ben Stokes drives it straight back to the bowler.

Anrich Nortje bowls this one full and angling into the pads, Ben Stokes clips this to deep mid-wicket and takes a single. That brings up the 100-run partnership between these two and they are slowly taking the game away from South Africa.
Short of a good length. Ben Foakes pulls it towards the square leg region for a single.
Goes a fraction fuller and just outside off, Ben Stokes gets a stride forward and blocks the ball to the right of the bowler.
Short of a good length, onto the leg stump. Ben Stokes works that one towards the fine leg region for a single.

Keshav Maharaj starts the over with a shortish delivery outside off, Ben Stokes shifts his weight on the back foot and thumps this towards deep cover-point. The ball does not have the legs to reach the boundary and they take three runs.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes tries to work it towards the off side but gets an inside edge the mid-wicket fielder.
What a beauty! Keshav Maharaj flights this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes comes forward to defend and gets beaten by the turn.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes defends it back to the bowler.

Keshav Maharaj fires this one short and angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes rocks back and hits the ball straight at Dean Elgar who is standing at silly point. He takes evasive action and turns around.
Short of a length. Ben Foakes stays on the back foot and defends it onto the pitch.
Anrich Nortje serves this on a good length and outside off,  Ben Stokes shoulders his arms to this one.
Fuller length, wide of off. Ben Stokes tries to drive this one towards cover but the ball goes off the outer half of the bat towards gully.
Pulls his length back a fraction, and bowls this outside off. Ben Stokes hits this on the up towards deep cover for a single.
Short of a length, down leg. Ben Foakes works it towards the fine leg region for a single.

Anrich Nortje goes really full outside the off stump, Ben Stokes strokes this towards deep cover. Does not connect as well as he would have liked as one hand comes off. They get a couple of runs in the process.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the mid on fielder for a single.
Keshav Maharaj sees Ben Stokes advance down the pitch and fires this one full and outside off, Ben Stokes digs this out to deep cover for a couple of runs.
Quicker and fuller this time. Ben Stokes goes onto the back foot and defends it down the pitch.
Bowls this a fraction short and outside off, keeps a touch low and Ben Stokes manages to cut this towards point. They run well to pick up a brace.
Short of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes tries to sweep that one but completely misses that one. A rare loose shot from Ben Stokes.
Continues to bowl short and outside off, Ben Stokes goes back in the crease and works the ball through covers for a run.
Short of length, outside off. Ben Foakes tries to work it towards the square leg region but the short leg fielder stops the ball.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a full delivery angling into the pads, Ben Stokes defends this to the left of the bowler towards mid on.
FOUR! Length delivery, outside off. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch and lofts it over the mid off fielder for a boundary. This one has been dispatched right from the middle of the bat.

Lungi Ngidi bowls a loopy delivery on a yorker length, and in line with the stumps, Ben Stokes gets his bat down to try and dig it out. The ball hits the pads and there is a massive appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Ben Stokes reviews right away! The replays show a massive inside edge onto pads and the third umpire does not even need to check UtraEdge. The decision has been reversed and Ben Stokes will continue to march on.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Ben Stokes defends it straight to the fielder at cover.
Lungi Ngidi goes for another slower delivery on a good length and outside off, Ben Stokes blocks this watchfully back to the bowler.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Stokes flicks it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Perfectly placed! A loopy delivery, outside off, fuller in length. Ben Stokes drives it powerfully through cover for a boundary.
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the point.

SIX! KABOOM! Ben Stokes is in the mood! Tosses it up, full and around off. Ben Stokes dances down the wicket, gets to the pitch of the ball, and smashes it over long off for a biggie. He moves onto 83!
'Round the wicket, outside off. Ben Stokes pushes it towards the cover for a single.
Quicker, flatter and shorter, around off. Ben Foakes looks to block this one but he gets an outside edge towards gully for a single.
Quicker and fuller this time. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and gets an outside edge down to point for a single.
Lungi Ngidi sprints in from 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, angling in, around off. Ben Stokes hangs back and defends it out.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Ben Stokes pushes it straight to the fielder at short mid wicket.
Beaten! Lovely ball! A good-length delivery, angling away, outside off. Ben Stokes looks to block this one away from his body but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short delivery, onto the leg stump. Ben Stokes gets inside the line and tucks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Swing and a miss! Outside off again, a length ball. Ben Foakes hangs back and tries to cut this one away but he fails to get any bat on it.

That is a well deserved half-century for Ben Foakes! He has played the perfect supporting role and has been patiently accumulating runs. This one is on a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes opens the bat face at the last minute and works it towards the third man region for a couple of runs.
Simon Harmer begins his over with a shorter ball, turning away, around middle. Ben Foakes pushes it back to the bowler.
Tad shorter, around the off pole. Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and punches it towards the cover fielder.
Fuller ball, tosses it up, around middle. Ben Stokes presses forward and blocks it out watchfully.
On a good length, around off. Ben Stokes plays this towards the backward point region for a single.
Loopy ball, full again, around middle. Ben Foakes flicks it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Fuller length, on the off stump line. Ben Foakes goes on the front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Angling away, a length ball, around off. Ben Stokes blocks it out towards the off side.
Fuller length, angling in. Ben Stokes pushes it with soft hand towards the cover region for a single.
Tailing back in, around middle and off, a length. Ben Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid on fielder.

A yorker-length delivery, outside off. Ben Foakes brings his bat down and tries to squeeze this one out, but he seems to have missed it. Kyle Verreynne fumbles a bit and collects the ball safely in the end. A huge appeal for caught behind as the players of South Africa think Foakes has got some bat on it. The replay shows that no bat was involved there. Not out it is!
Short of a good length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the cover region for a single.
Spinning in, shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes plays it towards the short leg fielder.
Back of a length, around off. Ben Foakes blocks it out watchfully off the back foot.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ben Foakes comes forward and flicks it to short mid wicket.
A shorter one, around middle and leg, Ben Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this a fraction short, outside off. Ben Foakes goes on the back foot and cuts it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Lungi Ngidi bowls a fuller ball, on the pads. Ben Stokes flicks it fine and towards fine leg for a boundary. He is into the 90s!

DROPPED! A big chance goes down! A tough chance though. Lungi Ngidi serves a fuller one, outside off. Ben Stokes dances down the pitch, makes room, and slices it towards cover. Aiden Markram there jumps high towards his right, and gets his hands to the ball but he fails to hold on to that one.
Two leg byes! Angling in now, a length ball, on the pads. Ben Stokes misses his flick and gets rapped on his pads. The ball rolls away towards mid-wicket and the batters take two runs.
On a length, around middle. Ben Stokes looks to block this one but he gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single. Ben Stokes moves onto 93!
Swinging away, fuller ball, around the off pole. Ben Foakes presses forward and blocks it out.
Darting this one on the pads, a good-length delivery. Ben Foakes tucks it towards square leg for a single.
No ball! Kagiso Rabada begins with a shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes gets on top of the bounce and keeps it out. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped here and a no ball is given.

Edged and safe! Another shorter ball, around leg. Ben Foakes looks to work it away towards the leg side but he gets a leading edge. The ball lobs up and falls in just short of the fielder at short cover.
Beaten! An absolute beauty by Kagiso Rabada! On a length, shaping away a tad, outside off. Ben Foakes stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge
Beaten again! This one comes back in, on a length, around off. Ben Foakes looks to defend this again, but he get beaten on the inside edge this time.
On a length, around middle. Ben Foakes keeps it out.
Shaping away, outside off, another good-length delivery. Ben Foakes is happy to let that one go away.
Kagiso Rabada delivers a length ball, around off. Ben Foakes keeps this one out.
A fuller ball, outside off. Ben Stokes drives it towards cover. Aiden Markram there dives to his left but fails to stop the ball cleanly. A single taken.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this on a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes taps this towards the gully fielder.
Straying down leg side on a fuller length, Ben Stokes does not connect his flick shot as it goes through to the keeper.
Bowls a yorker just outside off, Ben Foakes tries to dig this out but misses and the ball is collected by the keeper.
On a good length and angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this out towards short mid on.
This is a fraction full and outside off. Ben Foakes looks to work this leg side with the angle but gets a leading edge through cover-point for a single.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes works this towards the point fielder.
Going down leg side and delivered on a good length. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and collects this.
The single brings up the 300 for England! Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and angling into the pads, Ben Foakes clips this towards deep square leg for a run.
Kagiso Rabada goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander and bowls this short, outside off. Ben Stokes undercuts this towards point for a single.
This one is a touch fuller and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes clips the ball towards deep mid-wicket for three runs.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this outside off on a fuller length, Ben Stokes reaches for it and hits the ball wide of cover for a single.

Anrich Nortje begins with a full delivery angling into the pads from 'round the wicket. Ben Stokes looks to flick this but misses. Hits the pad and goes through to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne is convinced that there is some bat on this and convinces Dean Elgar to go for the review. UltraEdge shows a spike when the ball is near bat and pad, the third umpire reckons that it is only pad. Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the leg stump. Ben Stokes is safe and the on-field decision remains.
A shorter ball, sprays this one down leg. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery, around middle and off, angling away. Ben Stokes looks to block this one away but the ball goes off the outer half towards point for a single.
Anrich Nortje bangs it short again, on the body. Ben Foakes pulls this one towards the fielder at square leg.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Ben Foakes sways away from that one.
This is a fraction short and outside off, Ben Foakes mistimes his cut shot towards the point fielder.
Kagiso Rabada comes from 'round the wicket and bangs this in short outside off, Ben Stokes pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off, Ben Foakes defends this back down the pitch.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Foakes blocks this to the left of the bowler.
Kagiso Rabada goes full this time and down leg side, Ben Foakes lets this one go through to the keeper.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes tucks this to deep square leg for a single. Gives Ben Stokes one ball before Tea to get to his century.

No century for Ben Stokes in this session! Kagiso Rabada bowls a quick delivery nipping back in from 'round the wicket. Delivers this on a good length and just outside off. Ben Stokes gets beaten by the pace and the ball raps against his pads and goes through to the keeper. That will be TEA on Day 2.
A shorter ball, spinning in, around middle and leg. Ben Foakes flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Simon Harmer goes 'round the wicket, and delivers a shorter ball, darting it on the pads. Ben Stokes tucks it square of the wicket on the leg side for a single. Ben Stokes moves onto 99 now!
Fuller this time, around middle and off. Ben Foakes flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Ben Foakes advances down the pitch and works it away towards short mid-wicket.
This one drifts in, darting it on the pads. Ben Foakes tucks it towards short fine leg. No single there.
Tosses it up, around middle, full in length. Ben Foakes pushes it towards mid on.
Kagiso Rabada begins with a shorter ball, outside off. Ben Stokes blocks it out off the back foot.

There it is! A fuller ball, around middle. Ben Stokes drives it towards the bowler. The ball deflects off Kagiso Rabada's boot and goes towards square leg. A single taken. Ben Stokes brings up his 12th Test hundred and his first Ton as the England skipper. A classy knock from a classy player. He raises his bat and soaks in all the applause. He has taken England to a position of strength here.
FOUR! Nicely done! A length ball, outside off. Ben Foakes stays in his crease, opens the face of his bat and steers it towards third man.
A shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Kagiso Rabada bowls this a touch fuller and outside off, Ben Stokes works this to deep point and takes a run.
This one is wide outside off and served on a good length, Ben Foakes stands upright and leaves this one alone.
A tossed-up delivery, full, and around off. Ben Stokes knocks it towards long off for a single.
Full again, around middle, loopy ball. Ben Foakes blocks it out solidly.
Spinning in, around middle, full in length. Ben Foakes flicks it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Misfield and a run! Outside off, pitches it up. Ben Foakes steps down the pitch and works it away towards silly mid on. The fielder there fumbles to stop the ball and the batters cross ends.
Fuller one, spinning away, around middle. Ben Stokes advances down the pitch and eases it towards cover for an easy run.
Flights this one up, serves it full, around middle. Ben Foakes blocks it out.
An in-swinger, a length ball, around middle and leg. Ben Stokes looks to flick this one but he gets an inside edge onto his thigh pad.

OUT! TAKEN! A wicket finally for South Africa! Kagiso Rabada gets rid of Ben Stokes. The England skipper tries to take on Kagiso Rabada but he holes out. A length ball, around middle. Ben Stokes clears his front leg, and tries to hoick this one over mid-wicket. But the ball goes off the leading edge and flies high towards mid off. Dean Elgar there backtracks and takes a good catch. A terrific knock comes to an end. He walks off to a standing ovation.
Howout: c Dean Elgar b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary: On a length, outside off. Ben Foakes dabs it towards cover-point with soft hands and takes a single.
Swinging in, a length ball, around the thigh pad. Stuart Broad misses his flick and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Stuart Broad drives it towards cover off the front foot.
Swing and a miss! Shorter ball, around middle and leg. Stuart Broad advances down the pitch and looks to pull this one away but he misses it.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes shuffles down the wicket and flicks the ball to mid-wicket.
Bowls this a fraction short, Ben Foakes goes back in the crease and tucks the ball towards short leg.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and angled into the pads, Ben Foakes clips this down to the short leg fielder.
This is full on the pads, Ben Foakes clips this past backward square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Simon Harmer serves this full and outside off, Ben Foakes works this towards cover for a single.

SIX! BANG! Stuart Broad gets off the mark with a maximum. Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Stuart Broad charges down the wicket and thumps this straight back over the bowler for a biggie!
FOUR! Top shot! A shorter ball, around off. Ben Foakes picks up the length quickly and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Ben Foakes! Another shorter ball, around middle. Ben Foakes swivels and pulls it towards square leg. It's not from the middle of the bat but the ball will race away towards the boundary.
NO BALL! This is short as well and angled into the batter, Ben Foakes rocks back and pulls the ball to deep square leg for a single. Kagiso Rabada has overstepped and they get an extra run.
Bowls this on a good length and angling into the batter, Stuart Broad gives himself room and knocks the ball towards deep cover for a brace.
Continues to bowl on a good length and follows the batter to leg side. Stuart Broad backs away further and punches this towards deep cover. They take three runs this time.
This one is a touch fuller and outside off, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
This is one a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes knocks this to deep point and takes a run to keep strike.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes is down the wicket and flicks the ball to mid-wicket.
This is slightly short and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes tucks this to the right of mid-wicket and takes a single.
FOUR! Stuart Broad is playing quite a cameo! Simon Harmer bowls full on the pads, Stuart Broad sweeps this down to fine leg for a boundary.
Simon Harmer bowls this short and angling into the stumps, Stuart Broad uses the crease and punches the ball to deep cover for a single.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes tucks this around this leg towards short fine leg.
Loopy delivery bowled full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this back down the pitch.
Anrich Nortje begins with a good length delivery in line with the stumps, Stuart Broad makes room and swings his bat. Misses and the ball goes just over the stumps.

FOUR! Connects this one and sends it flying! Anrich Nortje bowls this a touch shorter and outside off, Stuart Broad slashes this over the infield, and the ball races to the deep point fence for four runs.
Anrich Nortje bowls this on a good length and follows the batter as he looks to make room, Stuart Broad mistimes his shot back towards the bowler.
Play and a miss! A shorter ball, angling away, outside off. Stuart Broad makes room and looks to pull this one but he fails to get any bat on it.
This one is on a good length as well and outside off, Stuart Broad gets an inside edge towards deep square leg for a single.
Anrich Nortje bowls this full on the pads, Ben Foakes flicks this towards mid-wicket and a misfield allows the to pick up three runs.
Simon Harmer bowls this full and outside off, Ben Foakes shimmies down the wicket once again and clips this towards mid on.
Another loopy ball, pitches it up again, around off. Ben Foakes advances down the pitch and works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! STUMPED! Stuart Broad's entertaining cameo comes to an end! Simon Harmer sees the batter charging and bowls this shorter outside off. Gets the ball to turn past the bat as Stuart Broad looks to heave this. Kyle Verreynne gets the ball and whips the bails off and the ball pops out of his hands. Stuart Broad has to depart and England have lost their seventh wicket and are 210 runs ahead.
Howout: st Kyle Verreynne b Simon Harmer

Commentary: Simon Harmer flights this one full and outside off, Ollie Robinson taps this towards point.
Simon Harmer floats this one outside off on a fuller length. Ollie Robinson goes for the reverse sweep on his second delivery and finds the backward point fielder.
Simon Harmer bowls an arm ball coming in from a fuller length, Ollie Robinson blocks the ball down to short leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Foakes dabs it towards cover-point and takes a single.
Short of a good length, onto the pads. Ollie Pope blocks it from within his crease.
Anrich Nortje drops it short, outside off. Ollie Robinson leans away and lets that go through to the keeper.
On a good length, outside off. Ollie Pope tries to swat that one away but misses it completely.
Oh, a nasty bouncer! Very short on this occasion, darting it around his helmet, at 143 clicks. Ollie Robinson does well to sways away from that one.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Ollie Pope pushes it straight towards the silly mid off fielder.
A touch quicker at 81 clicks, fuller one, drifting in, around middle. Ben Foakes does well to block this towards the off side.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes defends it on the front foot down the pitch.
Tosses this one up, sprays this one on the pads, full in length. Ben Foakes leans to flick this one but he gets a leading edge towards cover. A single taken.
Short and outside off. Ollie Pope goes on the back foot and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. They take three runs as the ball is stopped before the boundary.
Loopy ball, full and spinning away, outside off. Ben Foakes prods forward to block this but the ball goes off the outer half towards point. No run there!
Fuller, outside off. Ben Foakes knocks it towards the cover fielder.
FOUR! Ollie Robinson is not going to sway away from that one! A shorter ball, outside off. Ollie Robinson gets on his toes and upper-cuts it over the keeper's head for a boundary.
Fuller length, outside off. Ollie Robinson goes deep in the crease and dabs it towards cover for a single.
Beaten! A good ball from Anrich Nortje. On a length, around the fourth stump line. Ben Foakes looks to push this away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length, outside off. Ben Foakes plays and misses this one as it goes through to the keeper.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ben Foakes leans forward and drives it firmly through cover for a brace.
Short of a length, around the off stump channel. Ben Foakes tries to pull off the back foot but didn't time it well and it goes straight to the mid on fielder.
Tosses this one up, fuller in length, around middle and off. Ollie Robinson advances down the pitch and flicks it to the fielder at mid on.
Fuller length, onto the leg stump. Ollie Robinson tries to come down the track but adjust in the end to tuck it towards the square leg region.
A loopy ball, very full and around the leg pole. Ollie Robinson works it away towards mid-wicket for a single this time.
FOUR! Fuller length, onto the middle stump. Ben Foakes charges down the pitch and smokes it over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Fires this on his pads, a fuller ball. Ben Foakes clips it away through square leg for a single.
A fuller ball, tosses it up, around middle. Ollie Robinson advances down the pitch and lifts it over mid-wicket for a brace.
A length ball, angling in, on the pads. Ben Foakes works it away through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! This has been slapped away! Short ball, outside off. Ollie Robinson cuts it towards the point region for a boundary.
Swing and a miss! A good-length delivery, outside off. Ollie Robinson backs away and tries to chop this one away but he misses.
Full toss onto the pads. Ollie Robinson flicks it through square leg region for a couple of runs.
Edged and just short! Full and wide of off. Ollie Robinson manages to get an outside edge towards the slip cordon. The ball falls just short of the second slip fielder.
Fuller, outside off. Ollie Robinson drives it straight to the fielder at mid off. No run there!
Keshav Maharaj floats this one full and outside off, Ben Foakes gets a stride forward and knocks the ball to the cover fielder.
Short of a length, onto the stumps. Ben Foakes goes onto the back foot and defends it very comfortably.
A fraction short and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes goes back in the crease and taps the ball back to the bowler.
Fuller length, onto the middle and off. Ben Foakes defends on the front foot towards the cover.
Angles this one into the pads on a fuller length, Ben Foakes clips this wide of fine leg and takes a single.
Fuller one, slower through the air. Ollie Robinson watches it carefully and defends it down the pitch.
Anrich Nortje begins the over with a full delivery angling into the stumps, Ben Foakes flicks this towards mid on.
Fuller length, onto the off stump line. Ben Foakes  pushes it down to the fielder at mid off.
Anrich Nortje bowls this back of a length and angling down leg, Ben Foakes looks to glance this but misses and goes close to his gloves.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Foakes tries to pull the ball but mistimes it straight to the short mid-wicket fielder.

FOUR! Second Test century for Ben Foakes and his first one in England. He has played wonderfully and completely deserves the applause he is getting. Anrich Nortje bowls this a touch short and outside off, Ben Foakes cuts this fine towards the third man fence for a boundary!
Fuller length, outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it towards the mid off for a single and he will keep the strike.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes blocks this back towards the bowler.
Fuller, onto the leg stump line. Ben Foakes knocks it towards the long on fielder for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ollie Robinson has to depart and Keshav Maharaj gets his first wicket! Flights this one full and outside off, much slower through the air. Ollie Robinson looks to drive and gets an outside edge to first slip where Aiden Markram takes it comfortably. England lose their eight wicket now.
Howout: c Aiden Markram b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Fuller and slower through the air. Jack Leach tries to defend it and the ball hits his pad.
Keshav Maharaj bowls a quicker delivery full and outside off, Jack Leach gets on the front foot and blocks the ball to the off side.
Fuller, onto the stump. Jack Leach defends it down the ground.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a full delivery angling in from outside off, Ben Foakes clips this towards deep square leg and takes a single.
On a good length, angling in. Jack Leach tries to defend it and the ball hits the pads after the bat and rolls towards the slips.
Lungi Ngidi bowls this a fraction full and outside off, Jack Leach mistimes his shot towards point.
Swing and a miss. Fuller and outside off. Jack Leach tries to go big but misses that one completely.

FOUR! Jack Leach gets off the mark with a lucky boundary! Lungi Ngidi bowls this full and outside off, Jack Leach has room to free his arms and he takes a swipe at the ball. Gets the thickish edge that flies through the slip cordon and runs away to the fine leg boundary for four runs.
Play and miss. On a good length, outside off. Jack Leach tries to drive the ball through the cover but misses it completely.

Keshav Maharaj bowls this slow and flights this one full in line with the stumps, Ben Foakes shimmies down the wicket and lifts this high over the bowler's head. The ball lands just before the straight boundary and stops. They take two runs.

That is a missed opportunity! Keshav Maharaj sees the batter charging dwn the wicket and fires this one short and outside off, Ben Foakes swings but misses and Kyle Verreynne has to go wide to collect this. By the time he can get the ball back onto the stumps. Ben Foakes has made his ground.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this short and outside off, Ben Foakes punches this to deep cover for a single.
Keshav Maharaj bowls this a tad short and outside off, Jack Leach is on the back foot as he blocks this to the off side.

FOUR! This is audacious from Jack Leach! His teammates love it. Keshav Maharaj bowls this full and outside off, Jack Leach gets across to the off side and reverse sweeps this towards the deep cover fence for a boundary.
Flighted delivery bowled full outside off, Jack Leach is solid in defense as he blocks this firmly.
A length ball, angling in, on the thigh pad. Ben Foakes flicks it towards square leg for a single.
An overpitched delivery, around middle, at 137 clicks. Jack Leach drives it down the ground. Lungi Ngidi gets his right boot on the way and stops the ball.
Slightly shorter, on the thigh pad. Jack Leach does well to tuck this one away towards square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ben Foakes drives it firmly through cover for a brace.
Lungi Ngidi spills this one down leg, a shorter ball. Ben Foakes looks to pull this one but he misses.
Very short on this occasion, outside off. Ben Foakes hops and pulls it towards deep square leg. Two taken.
Keshav Maharaj comes in from over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, around middle. Jack Leach dances down the pitch and tonks it towards long on for a brace.
Tad shorter now, outside off. Jack Leach stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he misses.
Fuller, on middle. Jack Leach blocks it out.

OUT! TIMBER! Jack Leach departs and Ben Stokes calls his troops back in. Keshav Maharaj serves this a fraction short and in line with the stumps, Jack Leach charges down the wicket and misses the line as he tries to defend. The ball passes the outside edge and shatters the stumps. The lead is 264 and England want to have a bowl before Stumps.
Howout: b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: James Anderson bowls this on a good length and going down leg side, Sarel Erwee leaves this one alone.
Gets his line right this time as he serves this on a good length and outside off, Sarel Erwee lets this go through to the keeper.
James Anderson continues to bowl on a good length and outside off, Sarel Erwee decides to play at this late and blocks it to the off  side.
On a good length and in line with the stumps, Sarel Erwee blocks this back to the bowler.

Huge appeal from the fielders as the ball raps the pads. James Anderson bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Sarel Erwee misses the ball and gets hit on the pads. The umpire remains unmoved.
Bowls this on a good length as well and outside off, Sarel Erwee is watchful as he lets this go through.
Ollie Robinson begins with a good length delivery outside off, Dean Elgar leaves this one alone.
This one is a fraction short and in line with the stumps. Dean Elgar blocks this towards short leg.
Ollie Robinson goes a bit fuller and outside off, Dean Elgar gets a thick edge that goes through the backward point region for a couple of runs.
Oh, well bowled! A shorter ball, angling in, outside off. Dean Elgar looks to tuck this one on the leg side, but he gets beaten on the inside edge.
Fuller ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leans forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Bowls this on a good length and pitching around leg, Dean Elgar defends this from deep in his crease.

A length ball, around middle and leg, swinging away a tad. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he misses and gets hit on his pads. A huge shout for LBW, and the umpire says no!  Ben Stokes decides to go up for the review. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking indicates that it was pitching outside leg. The on-field decision stands and England lose a review.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
FOUR! Oh, shot! A pitched-up delivery, around middle. Sarel Erwee shows the full face of the bat and drives it straight down the ground for a glorious boundary.
Slight back of a length now, outside off. Sarel Erwee hops and pushes it towards point for a single.
James Anderson sprays this one down the leg side, a length ball. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Shorter one again, around middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out watchfully.
Ollie Robinson speeds in from over the wicket and serves a fuller ball, angling away, outside off. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
On a length, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee tucks it past short leg. Three taken.
Change of angle now! Ollie Robinson comes in from 'round the wicket, he bowls a length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar offers no shot to that.
Another good-length delivery, outside off, at 130 clicks. Dean Elgar is happy to let that one go through to the keeper.
Angling in, tad shorter, around middle. Dean Elgar taps it towards short leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar stands tall and punches it off the back foot through cover-point for a brace.
Jack Leach begins with a shorter ball, around off. Sarel Erwee hangs back and defends it out watchfully.
A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire once again disagrees. A loopy one this one, full and spinning in, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and pads it away. That was probably missing wickets.
Quicker and flatter, around middle. Sarel Erwee defends it out solidly off the back foot.
Fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and drives it towards cover for a single.
Shorter ball, turning in, around middle. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and tucks it towards square leg.
Back of a length, turning in, around middle. Dean Elgar rocks back and turns it away towards mid-wicket.
Slightly short in length, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it off the back foot towards cover. A single taken.
Ollie Robinson comes in from 'round the wicket and bowls a shortish ball, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and tries to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, around middle and off. Dean Elgar blocks it out watchfully.
Angling in, on the pads, a length ball. Dean Elgar turns it towards backward square leg.
Tight leave! An in-swinger, around the fourth stump line, a length ball. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it.
Good-length delivery, nipping back in, around middle. Dean Elgar taps it towards mid-wicket. A testing over from Ollie Robinson.
Shorter one, spinning in, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays in his crease and blocks it towards the bowler.
Quicker at 88 clicks, flatter and outside off. Sarel Erwee rocks back and blocks it towards the fielder at point.
Tosses it up this time, a fuller one, outside off. Sarel Erwee lunges forward and defends it out.
Quick and short, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends it towards cover off the back foot.
Loopy one, full in length, outside off. Sarel Erwee presses forward and defends it out watchfully.
Jack Leach flights this one up, serves it full and on middle. Sarel Erwee prods forward and defends this one.
FOUR! Nicely done! An overpitched delivery, darting it on the pads. Dean Elgar uses his wrists and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

Oh, a peach of a delivery! This one lands on a length, jags away, a tad, outside off. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and looks to block this one but he gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar gets on his toes and taps it towards cover-point for a single.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends this one towards the cover region.
Ollie Robinson pulls his length back a tad, and serves it outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it off the back foot through cover for a brace.
Another length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee hangs back and taps it towards mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, full, around middle. Dean Elgar leans forward and blocks it out.
Spinning in, a fuller ball, on the pads. Dean Elgar leans to tuck this one away but he misses. The ball lobs up off his pads and goes towards short leg.
Shorter one, spinning in, around middle. Dean Elgar rocks back and defends it out.
Edgy runs! A shorter one, spinning in, around off. Dean Elgar rocks back and looks to block this one but the ball goes off the outside edge and away from the fielder at first slip. Two taken!
Back of a length again, around middle. Dean Elgar blocks this one off the back foot towards short leg.
Fuller one, outside off, spinning in. Dean Elgar leans across and pads this one away. That will be Stumps on Day 2!
Joe Root begins with a full delivery angling down leg, Sarel Erwee looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Sarel Erwee blocks this back down the pitch.
Floats this one full and outside off, Sarel Erwee strokes this straight to short mid off.
Joe Root bowls this one full and drifting into the pads, Sarel Erwee taps this to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! Finds the gap with perfection! Joe Root flights this one full and outside off, Sarel Erwee gets a stride forward and hits it with the turn. Finds the gap in the packed off side field and the ball races to the deep cover fence for the first boundary of the morning.
Fires this one full and into the legs, Sarel Erwee clips this through square leg for a single.
James Anderson begins with a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
On a length again, around middle. Sarel Erwee blocks it watchfully.
Tighter line! Around the fifth stump line, length ball. Sarel Erwee is happy to let that one go.

Good shot! A fuller ball, outside off, at 131 clicks. Sarel Erwee leans forward and drives this one away from his body through cover. Jack Leach chases the ball and keeps it away from the boundary ropes. Three taken.
Leg bye! Darting it on the thigh pad, a length ball from 'round the wicket. Dean Elgar looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball goes off the thigh pad towards square leg a leg bye taken.
Beaten! Lovely ball! On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Joe Root tosses this one up, serves it full, spinning away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Another fuller ball, around middle. Dean Elgar prods forward and blocks it out.
Loopy one, turning away, around off. Dean Elgar leans forward and defends it towards cover.
Tad shorter now, around the off pole. Dean Elgar rocks back and pushes it towards cover.
Extra bounce there! Tad shorter, outside off, spinning away. Dean Elgar looks to play at it but bails out in the end due to the extra bounce.
Joe Root flights this one up, serves it full and outside off. Dean Elgar lunges forward and drives it to the fielder at cover.
James Anderson speeds in from over the wicket, and bowls a length ball, outside off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
This one jags back in a tad, full and around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee works it away through square leg. Only a single.
Change of angle now! James Anderson sprints in from 'round the wicket, he delivers a good-length delivery, angling in, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar tucks it awkwardly towards square leg.
Beaten! Lovely ball! A length ball, this one nips away after pitching, outside off. Dean Elgar gets beaten while trying to block this one.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! James Anderson draws first blood! He gets rid of the South African skipper, Dean Elgar. Another beauty by Anderson. Another length ball, swinging away, on the off pole. Dean Elgar once again tries to defend this one, but he gets beaten on the outside edge. The ball goes on and uproots the off pole. England are up and running early in the day! A perfect start for them.
Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary: James Anderson comes from over the wicket, outside off, a length ball. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Ollie Robinson runs in from over the wicket and serves a length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee is happy to let that one go.
On a length again, outside off. Sarel Erwee does not fiddle with that one.
This one angles in, on a length, around middle. Sarel Erwee blocks it back to the bowler.
Bowls a good-length delivery, outside off, at 131 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.

Oh, close call! On a length, jagging in a bit, around middle. Sarel Erwee looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball hit him near his thigh pad and rolls slowly towards the stump. Sarel Erwee is well aware and he moves the ball away from the stumps with his bat.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee defends it out towards cover. A maiden over to begin with for Ollie Robinson.
A fuller ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen miscues his drives towards mid off and takes a single. He gets off the mark with that.
James Anderson comes in from 'round the wicket to Sarel Erwee now. He bowls a length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee is solid in his defense.
Beaten! A peach! Another length ball, outside off, angling in. Sarel Erwee looks to defend this but he gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
Angling in again, around middle and leg this time, a length ball. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Tight leave! On a length, swinging in, outside off. Keegan Petersen leans forward and shoulders his arms at it.
Fuller delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen prods forward and eases it towards mid off.
Ollie Robinson bowls this a fraction full and outside off, Sarel Erwee knocks this towards the cover fielder.

Edged and just short! Ollie Robinson continues bowling a touch fuller and outside off, Sarel Erwee pushes hard at this and gets an edge that falls just short of the second slip fielder diving to his right. Close call for Sarel Erwee.
This is on a good length and outside off, Sarel Erwee blocks this towards cover.
Ollie Robinson continues to bowl on a good length but this is wider outside the off stump, Sarel Erwee leaves this one alone.

Ollie Robinson gets another edge. Ollie Robinson bowls this full once more and just outside off, Sarel Erwee looks to defend and gets an outside edge that flies through the slip cordon for a boundary to third man.
Delivers this closer to the off stump on a good length. Keegan Petersen gets an inside edge towards backward square leg and takes a run to keep strike.
James Anderson bowls this on a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen blocks this towards the mid off fielder.
Continues bowling on a good length and wider outside off, Keegan Petersen shoulders his arms to this one.
Just outside the off stump and on a good length. This is defended to the left of the bowler.
James Anderson sticks to bowling on a good length and outside the off pole. Keegan Petersen works this towards point.
Goes a fraction fuller and gets this one to angle into the stumps from outside off, Keegan Petersen defends this watchfully towards the short mid on fielder.
James Anderson goes back to bowling on a good length and in line with the off stump, Keegan Petersen looks to block and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Ollie Robinson serves this on a good length and angling away from the left-hander from over the wicket. Sarel Erwee leaves this one as it goes through to the keeper.
Wide outside off on a good length, Sarel Erwee happy to let this one go as well.
Decides to go 'round the wicket now and angles this ball in from outside off, Sarel Erwee defends this towards the cover fielder.
Back to over the wicket and bowls this on a good length, outside off. Sarel Erwee is back to leaving the ball this alone.
Ollie Robinson seems to be a bit confused as he goes 'round the wicket once more. This is angling in from outside off, Sarel Erwee blocks this confidently towards cover.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ollie Robinson tries everything and finally gets the breakthrough! He bowls this on a good length and just outside off from 'round the wicket. Sarel Erwee feels for the ball and then decides to leave it alone. The decision is late as he gets a faint nick through to the keeper. Ben Foakes makes no mistake behind the wicket as he grabs onto this. South Africa is in all sorts of trouble now as both the openers have departed.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: James Anderson bowls this a touch short and outside off, Keegan Petersen gets on his toes and punches this straight past mid on for a brace.
On a good length and outside off, Keegan Petersen plays this with a cross bat and guides the ball to third man for a single.
This one is on a good length as well and outside off, Keegan Petersen blocks this towards backward point.
Continues bowling on a good length and this is a bit outside off, Keegan Petersen does not want to play at this.

James Anderson bowls this a fraction fuller and outside off, gets the ball to skid after pitching. Keegan Petersen looks to push this one away and gets beaten on the outside edge. Ben Foakes is celebrating and James Anderson is sure this is out. The umpire raises his finger and Keegan Petersen reviews immediately. UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved and the onfield decision has to be reversed. Keegan Petersen will continue and South Africa will be hoping it is for a long time hereafter.
Shorter ball, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen gets on top of the bounce and blocks it out.
Ollie Robinson begins the over with a full delivery in line with the stumps, Aiden Markram digs this out and knocks the ball to mid off.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps, Aiden Markram stands tall and blocks the ball back to the bowler.
Continues to serve this on a good length and outside off, Aiden Markram works this towards cover-point.
Ollie Robinson attacking the outside off stump line on a good length. Aiden Markram guides this towards backward point.

What a delivery! Ollie Robinson delivers this on a good length and gets the ball to nip back in sharply. Aiden Markram raises his arms and does really well to leave this one alone as it goes over the stumps.
Another ball that nips back into the batter. This is a fraction outside off on a good length. Aiden Markram shoulders arms to this one as well.
Stuart Broad begins with a fuller ball, outside off, this one keeps low as well. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
On a good length, outside off. Keegan Petersen punches it straight to the fielder at cover.
A length ball, this one slants in, around middle. Keegan Petersen works it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller length, outside off. Aiden Markram let's that ball go through to the keeper.

No ball! OH, dear! Wicket...but it's no ball. What a peach of a delivery by Stuart Broad! A length ball, nipping back in, on the off pole. Aiden Markram looks to block this one but he misses and the ball clips the off stump. England players are celebrating, but the umpires signal a no ball. Stuart Broad has overstepped here. Aiden Markram had started walking back but he comes back to bat.
FOUR! Adding salt to injury! A length ball, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a good length, outside off. Aiden Markram pushes it straight to the fielder at cover.
No ball! Tad shorter, outside off. Keegan Petersen stays in his crease and pushes it towards cover. Ollie Robinson has overstepped here and a no ball is called.
Pitches this one up, outside off. Aiden Markram leans forward and drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Aiden Markram cuts it towards the point fielder for a single.
Angling away, fuller one, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it towards cover-point.
Short of a length, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen gets an inside edge on his pads and the ball rolls towards the square leg region for a single.
Tight leave! A length, nipping in, outside off. Aiden Markram watches it sail through to the keeper.
On a good length, onto the off pole. Aiden Markram pushes it towards the cover for a quick single.
A good-length delivery, jagging back in, around the off pole. Aiden Markram blocks it out off the back foot.
On a good length, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves that one very easily straight to the keeper.
Another length delivery, tailing back in, around middle and leg. Aiden Markram tucks it towards mid-wicket.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKE! Stuart Broad gets his man this time! He checks with the umpire if that's a no ball and the umpire shows him thumps up. Lovely ball from Broad. A typical test match line. Fuller length outside off. Aiden Markram tries to drive it towards cover and gets an outside edge straight to Zak Crawley at second slip who takes a good sharp catch. South Africa have lost their third wicket and England continues to dominate this game.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Play and a miss. On a good length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen tries to defend it but gets beaten by the swing straight into the hand of the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and dabs it towards point.
FOUR BYES! Fuller length, drifting down the leg. Keegan Petersen misses his flick and the keeper tries to stop that one but it sneaks through his gloves towards the fine leg for a boundary.
Another shorter ball, around off. Keegan Petersen gets on top of the bounce and defends it out.
Back of length, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen pulls it towards square leg for a single and it's a no ball as well for overstepping.
An appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no! A length ball, swinging in, on the pads. Rassie van der Dussen misses his flick and gets rapped on his pads. That was sliding down leg.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
On a good length, onto the off stump line. Rassie van der Dussen gets on the back foot and defends it back to the bowler.
A yorker-length delivery to begin with, around off. Keegan Petersen brings his bat down to dig this one out but the ball goes off the inside edge towards short leg.
A length ball, around middle and off. Keegan Petersen stays in his crease and punches it towards cover.
Fuller one again, outside off. Keegan Petersen leans forward and drives it towards mid off.
A good-length ball, onto the stumps. Keegan Petersen defends it straight to Ollie Pope at silly mid on.
Another pitched-up delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen is happy to let that one go.
On a good length, onto the stumps. Keegan Petersen defends it solidly back to the bowler.
Jack Leach bowls this full and angling down leg, Rassie van der Dussen puts his pad on it and the ball rolls to short fine leg.
Fuller length, onto the off stump line. Rassie van der Dussen pushes it towards mid off.
Jack Leach serves this one full and in line with the stumps, Rassie van der Dussen smothers this into the pitch.
Pitched up, onto the middle stump. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and defends it.
This one is a bit short and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets low and cuts the ball to deep cover-point for a single.
Fuller length, onto the middle stump. Keegan Petersen goes deep in his crease and defends it onto the pitch.
Stuart Broad serves this on a good length and outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves this one alone and the ball stays a touch low. Ben Foakes does well to collect this behind the wicket.
On a good length, onto the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen gets in the line and defends it solidly.

FOUR! Rassie van der Dussen will take on the short ball! Stuart Broad bangs this into the pitch and angles the ball towards the leg side. Rassie van der Dussen swivels and looks to pull, gets a top edge that flies straight to fine leg for a boundary.
Fuller length, angling in. Rassie van der Dussen tries to go through the off side but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Goes a touch fuller and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen decides to leave this at the last moment.
On a good length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen rocks back and defends it solidly.
Jack Leach bowls this quicker and in line with the stumps, Keegan Petersen rocks back and punches the ball to the cover fielder.
Slower through the air, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards the short leg region.
Flights this one full and in line with the off stump, Keegan Petersen gets a big stride forward and blocks the ball to the left of the bowler.
Short of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen tries to cut it but gets an outside edge and the ball races away towards the third man region for a couple.
Goes back to bowling full and straight in line with the stumps, Keegan Petersen blocks and gets a outside edge towards point.
Short of a length, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen goes on the back foot and punches it towards extra-cover.

FOUR! Another edge gets South Africa a boundary! Stuart Broad bowls this a bit full and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets all squared up and hangs his bat out. Gets a thick edge and flies in the vacant third slip area for a boundary to third man.
On a good length, onto the middle stump line. Rassie van der Dussen defends it towards short mid wicket.
This is on a good length and just outside off, Rassie van der Dussen stands upright and blocks the ball back towards the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen let's it go to the keeper.
Stuart Broad bowls this on a good length and angling in from outside off, Rassie van der Dussen knocks this wide off mid on and takes a run.
Fuller length, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Jack Leach begins the over with a full delivery in line with the stumps, Rassie van der Dussen solid in defense as he blocks the ball into the pitch towards the leg side.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen defends solidly off the front foot.
This is a fraction short and straight onto middle, Rassie van der Dussen gets back in the crease and defends this back down the pitch.
Fuller length, onto the leg stump. Rassie van der Dussen knocks it towards the mid-wicket region.
Goes full and just outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets his front foot forward and pushes at the ball. Gets an inside edge towards short fine leg.
Fuller length, onto the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it off the front foot down on the pitch.
Stuart Broad bowls this slightly back of a length and outside off, Keegan Petersen gets on his toes and punches the ball wide of the cover fielder for a single.
Fuller length, onto the stump, this one keeps low as well. Rassie van der Dussen does well to block this one.
This one is on a good length and outside off, Rassie van der Dussen leaves this one alone.
Back of length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen goes on the back foot and tucks it towards the short midwicket.
This one keeps a touch low from a good length and outside the off stump. Rassie van der Dussen manages to block this towards cover-point.
Fuller length, around the off pole. Rassie van der Dussen drives it straight to the fielder at mid on.

FOUR! Joe Root begins with a freebie! Bowls a full toss outside off, Keegan Petersen gets a stride forward and punches the ball into the vacant mid off region for a boundary to long off. That should release some pressure.
Fuller length, outside off. Keegan Petersen pushes it towards the silly mid off straight into the hands of the fielder.
Joe Root floats this one full and outside off, Keegan Petersen gets his front foot forward confidently and strokes the ball towards deep cover for a couple of runs.
Fuller length, onto the stump. Keegan Petersen knocks it towards the short mid-wicket.
Joe Root fires this full and angles it into the pads, Keegan Petersen clips this towards the short mid-wicket.
Joe Root this time comes 'round the wicket. Bowls a fuller length delivery, onto the leg stump line. Keegan Petersen works it towards the square leg region for a single.
Jack Leach bowls this quicker and serves it full and into the pads, Keegan Petersen flicks this to mid-wicket.
Short of length, onto the leg stump. Keegan Petersen goes on the backfoot and punches it towards the short mid wicket.
This is full and outside off, Keegan Petersen misjudges the length and goes back. Gets his bat down in time and gets an outside edge towards short third man.
Short of a length, onto the stump. Keegan Petersen goes on the back foot and defends it straight towards short leg fielder.
This is full and outside off, Keegan Petersen blocks the ball to the off side.
Fuller length, onto the stump. Keegan Petersen transfers his weight on the front foot and defends it.
Joe Root bowls this full and on a leg stump line, Rassie van der Dussen blocks this down to short leg.
Fuller length, onto the stumps. Rassie van der Dussen defends solidly towards the off side region.
Fires this one full and into the pads, Rassie van der Dussen clips the ball towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Fuller length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen drives it towards the vacant cover area for a handsome boundary.
Joe Root flights this one full and just outside off, Rassie van der Dussen gets forward and blocks the ball down the pitch towards the bowler.
Fuller length, attacking the stumps. Rassie van der Dussen defends on the front foot towards the short leg fielder.
Jack Leach fires this one full and going well down leg stump, Keegan Petersen makes room and tries to flick this but misses. Gets hit on the pads.
Fuller length, onto the pads. Jack Leach bowls that one quicker and it hits the batters pad.
This is a fraction short and fired down leg, Keegan Petersen goes right back in the crease and blocks this ball towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller length, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives of the front foot but a good stop by the fielder at cover.

Bowls this one short and spinning down leg, Keegan Petersen looks to flick this but misses. Ben Foakes makes a huge appeal but the bowler does not seem interested. The umpire agrees with the bowler and says not out.
